## Error handling

- Use centralized error-handling middleware; controllers should `throw` or `next(err)` instead of sending ad-hoc error responses.
- Always include helpful error messages but never leak stack traces or secrets in responses.

## Validation & security

- Validate all external input (body, query, params) in `validators/` before hitting services.
- Sanitize inputs where relevant and guard against NoSQL/SQL injection.
- Require auth middleware for any route that mutates data.

## Code style

- Use async/await only; avoid raw Promise chains.
- No `any` in TypeScript; prefer precise types or `unknown` with narrowing.
